name: Bench Press
description: The bench press is a compound exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps. It involves lying on a bench and lifting a weight barbell above the chest. Bench press is a fundamental strength training exercise and is popular in both powerlifting and bodybuilding.

name: Cable Crossover
description: Cable crossovers are an isolation exercise that targets the chest muscles. It involves pulling two cable handles together in a crossing motion, providing constant tension on the chest throughout the movement.

name: Dumbbell Flyes
description: Dumbbell flyes are an isolation exercise that focuses on stretching and contracting the chest muscles. It involves lying on a flat bench and lifting dumbbells in a wide arc motion.

name: Incline Dumbbell Press
description: The incline dumbbell press targets the upper chest muscles. It involves lying on an incline bench and pressing dumbbells upward in a controlled motion.

name: Decline Dumbbell Bench Press
description: The decline dumbbell bench press targets the lower chest muscles. It involves lying on a decline bench and pressing dumbbells upward in a controlled motion.

name: Machine Fly
description: The machine fly is a chest isolation exercise that utilizes a machine with arms that move in a controlled motion, allowing for a focused chest workout.

name: Cable Fly
description: Cable fly is an isolation exercise that targets the chest muscles. It involves pulling cable handles together in front of the body, providing constant tension on the chest.

name: Cable Press
description: Cable press is a chest exercise that involves pushing cable handles away from the body. It provides constant resistance throughout the movement.

name: Low Cable Crossover
description: Low cable crossover is an exercise that targets the lower chest muscles. It involves pulling cable handles from a low position to the center of the body.

name: Machine Bench Press
description: Machine bench press is a chest exercise performed on a machine. It mimics the motion of a traditional bench press and is suitable for beginners.

name: Smith Machine Incline Bench Press
description: Smith machine incline bench press targets the upper chest muscles. It involves lifting a barbell on a guided track in an inclined position.

name: Decline Barbell Bench Press
description: Decline barbell bench press targets the lower chest muscles. It involves lifting a barbell while lying on a decline bench.

name: Close Grip Dumbbell Press
description: Close grip dumbbell press is an exercise that targets the triceps and inner chest. It involves pressing dumbbells together in a close grip.

name: Cable Chest Press
description: Cable chest press is an exercise that involves pushing cable handles away from the body in a horizontal motion. It targets the chest muscles.

name: Squat
description: Squat is a compound exercise that targets the muscles of the lower body, including quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. It involves bending the knees and hips to lower the body into a sitting position.

name: Walking Lunges
description: Walking lunges are a dynamic exercise that works the muscles of the legs, particularly the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. It involves taking steps forward and lowering the body into a lunge position.

name: Front Barbell Squat
description: Front barbell squat is a variation of the traditional squat where the barbell is positioned in front of the body. It targets the muscles of the lower body, including quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes.

name: Leg Press
description: Leg press is a resistance training exercise that targets the muscles of the lower body, including quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. It involves pushing a weighted platform away from the body using the legs.

name: Sumo Squat
description: Sumo squat is a variation of the squat that targets the inner thighs and works the muscles of the lower body, including quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. It involves a wide stance with toes pointed outward.

name: Leg Curl
description: Leg curl is an isolation exercise that targets the hamstrings. It involves flexing the knees to curl a weight towards the buttocks while lying face down on a leg curl machine.

name: Barbell Glute Bridge
description: Barbell glute bridge is an exercise that targets the glutes and hamstrings. It involves lying on the ground with a barbell across the hips and lifting the hips towards the ceiling.

name: Leg Extension
description: Leg extension is an isolation exercise that targets the quadriceps. It involves extending the legs against resistance while seated on a leg extension machine.

name: Kettlebell Swing
description: Kettlebell swing is a dynamic exercise that targets the posterior chain, including the hips, glutes, and hamstrings. It involves swinging a kettlebell between the legs and up to chest height.

name: Sumo Deadlift
description: Sumo deadlift is a variation of the traditional deadlift that targets the muscles of the lower body, including the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back. It involves a wide stance with toes pointed outward.

name: Reverse Hyperextension
description: Reverse hyperextension is an exercise that targets the lower back and hamstrings. It involves lying face down on a hyperextension bench and lifting the legs towards the ceiling.

name: Deadlift
description: Deadlift is a compound exercise that targets the muscles of the lower back, glutes, hamstrings, and core. It involves lifting a loaded barbell from the ground to a standing position.

name: Bicep Curl
description: Bicep curl is an isolation exercise that targets the biceps. It involves flexing the elbow to curl a weight towards the shoulders.

name: Barbell Curl
description: Barbell curl is a compound exercise that targets the biceps. It involves flexing the elbow to curl a barbell towards the shoulders.

name: Incline Dumbbell Curl
description: Incline dumbbell curl is a variation of the bicep curl performed on an incline bench. It targets the biceps and emphasizes the stretch in the muscle.

name: Hammer Curl
description: Hammer curl is a bicep exercise that also targets the brachialis and brachioradialis muscles. It involves holding the dumbbells in a neutral grip and curling them towards the shoulders.

name: Concentration Curls
description: Concentration curls are an isolation exercise that targets the biceps. It involves sitting on a bench and curling a dumbbell with a focused, concentrated movement.

name: Overhead Cable Curl
description: Overhead cable curl is an isolation exercise that targets the biceps. It involves pulling a cable attachment down from an overhead position while standing.

name: Spider Curl
description: Spider curl is a bicep exercise performed on a preacher bench. It involves lying face down on the bench and curling a barbell or dumbbells.

name: Zottman Curl
description: Zottman curl is a bicep exercise that combines a traditional curl with a reverse grip. It targets the biceps and forearms.

name: Cross Body Hammer Curl
description: Cross body hammer curl is a variation of the hammer curl where the dumbbell is curled across the body, targeting the biceps and forearms.

name: Waiter Curl
description: Waiter curl is an isolation exercise for the biceps. It involves holding a dumbbell with an overhand grip and curling it towards the shoulder like a waiter carrying a tray.

name: One Arm Dumbbell Preacher Curl
description: One arm dumbbell preacher curl is an isolation exercise for the biceps performed on a preacher bench. It involves curling a dumbbell with one arm at a time.

name: Cable Hammer Curls Rope Attachment
description: Cable hammer curls with rope attachment are an isolation exercise for the biceps. It involves using a cable machine with a rope attachment to curl the weight.

name: Machine Bicep Curl
description: Machine bicep curl is an isolation exercise for the biceps performed on a machine. It involves curling a lever arm against resistance.

name: Lying Triceps Extension
description: Lying triceps extension is an isolation exercise that targets the triceps. It involves lowering a weight behind the head while lying on a bench.

name: Overhead Triceps Extension
description: Overhead triceps extension is an isolation exercise that targets the triceps. It involves extending the arms overhead with a weight.

name: Close Grip Bench Press
description: Close grip bench press is a compound exercise that targets the triceps. It involves performing a bench press with a narrow grip.

name: Push Down
description: Push down is an isolation exercise that targets the triceps. It involves pushing a cable attachment down towards the ground.

name: Tricep Dips
description: Tricep dips are a bodyweight exercise that targets the triceps. It involves lowering and raising the body using parallel bars.

name: Dip
description: Dip is a bodyweight exercise that targets the triceps. It involves lowering and raising the body using parallel bars.

name: Close Grip Dumbbell Press
description: Close grip dumbbell press is an exercise that targets the triceps and inner chest. It involves pressing dumbbells together in a close grip.

name: Cable Rope Overhead Triceps Extension
description: Cable rope overhead triceps extension is an isolation exercise that targets the triceps. It involves pulling a rope attachment down from an overhead position.

name: TRX Tricep Extension
description: TRX tricep extension is a bodyweight exercise that targets the triceps. It involves extending the arms while suspended from TRX straps.

name: Cable Tricep Kickback
description: Cable tricep kickback is an isolation exercise that targets the triceps. It involves extending the arm back with a cable attachment.

name: Lateral Raise
description: Lateral raise is an isolation exercise that targets the lateral head of the shoulder muscles. It involves lifting the arms out to the sides against resistance.

name: Front Raise
description: Front raise is an isolation exercise that targets the front head of the shoulder muscles. It involves lifting the arms to the front against resistance.

name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
description: Dumbbell shoulder press is a compound exercise that targets the shoulders. It involves pressing dumbbells overhead from shoulder level.

name: Barbell Upright Row
description: Barbell upright row is a compound exercise that targets the shoulders and traps. It involves lifting a barbell towards the chin with a narrow grip.

name: Reverse Fly
description: Reverse fly is an isolation exercise that targets the rear head of the shoulder muscles. It involves lifting the arms out to the sides against resistance while bent over.

name: Arnold Press
description: Arnold press is a shoulder exercise that involves a combination of lateral and front raises with rotation. It targets various parts of the shoulder muscles.

name: Barbell Rear Delt Raise
description: Barbell rear delt raise is an isolation exercise that targets the rear head of the shoulder muscles. It involves lifting a barbell to the rear while bent over.

name: One-arm Dumbbell Row
description: One-arm dumbbell row is a unilateral exercise that targets the muscles of the upper back. It involves pulling a dumbbell towards the hip while keeping the back straight.

name: Row
description: Row is a compound exercise that primarily targets the muscles of the upper back. It involves pulling a weight towards the body using a variety of equipment, such as a barbell or cable machine.

name: Dumbbell Pullover
description: Dumbbell pullover is an isolation exercise that targets the muscles of the upper body, including the chest, lats, and triceps. It involves extending a dumbbell over the head while lying on a bench.

name: Barbell Deadlift
description: Barbell deadlift is a compound exercise that targets the muscles of the lower back, hamstrings, and glutes. It involves lifting a loaded barbell from the ground to a standing position.

name: Meadows Row
description: Meadows row is a variation of the one-arm dumbbell row developed by bodybuilder John Meadows. It targets the lats and upper back muscles. It involves a unique body positioning to emphasize muscle engagement.

name: One-arm Lat Pulldown
description: One-arm lat pulldown is a unilateral exercise that targets the lats and upper back. It involves pulling a cable attachment down towards the hip while sitting or standing.

name: Landmine Row
description: Landmine row is a compound exercise that targets the upper back, lats, and rear delts. It involves rowing a barbell attached to a landmine apparatus.

name: Back Rows
description: Back rows is a general term for various rowing exercises that target the muscles of the upper back. It can include exercises like barbell rows, cable rows, and machine rows.

name: Close-grip Front Lat Pulldown
description: Close-grip front lat pulldown is a variation of the lat pulldown that emphasizes the inner portion of the lats. It involves pulling a cable attachment down in front of the body with a close grip.

name: Pull-down
description: Pull-down is a general term for exercises that involve pulling a weight down towards the body. It can refer to various lat pulldown variations using different grips and equipment.
